{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' __issue_context__.json\"","aggregated_output":"{\n  \"body\": \"This term has no enzyme xref: \\n\\nid: GO:0043713\\nname: (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate dehydrogenase activity\\nnamespace: molecular_function\\ndef: \\\"Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoisocaproate + NADH + H+ = (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate + NAD+.\\\" [GOC:jl, PMID:16957230]\\nis_a: GO:0016616 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-OH group of donors, NAD or NADP as acceptor\\n\\n\\nBut \\\"(R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate dehydrogenase\\\" is a synonym of EC:1.1.1.345 D-2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase (NAD(+)), which equates with this GO term:\\n\\nid: GO:0140175\\nname: (2R)-2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity\\nnamespace: molecular_function\\ndef: \\\"Catalysis of the reaction: a (2R)-2-hydroxycarboxylate + NAD+ = a 2-oxocarboxylate + NADH + H+.\\\" [RHEA:35643]\\nxref: EC:1.1.1.345 {source=\\\"skos:exactMatch\\\"}\\nxref: RHEA:10052 {source=\\\"skos:narrowMatch\\\"}\\nxref: RHEA:35643 {source=\\\"skos:exactMatch\\\"}\\nxref: RHEA:57408 {source=\\\"skos:narrowMatch\\\"}\\nxref: RHEA:70327 {source=\\\"skos:narrowMatch\\\"}\\nxref: RHEA:86067 {source=\\\"skos:narrowMatch\\\"}\\nxref: RHEA:86071 {source=\\\"skos:narrowMatch\\\"}\\nis_a: GO:0016616 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-OH group of donors, NAD or NADP as acceptor\\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \\\"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30138\\\" xsd:anyURI\\n\\nAlso, a search of CHEBI with '(R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate' returns:\\nCHEBI:55534 - (R)-2-hydroxy-4-methylpentanoic acid\\n\\nAnd one of the narrowMatch RHEA xrefs is:\\nRHEA:10052\\n(2R)-hydroxy-4-methylpentanoate + NAD(+) = 4-methyl-2-oxopentanoate + NADH + H(+)\\n\\nand (2R)-hydroxy-4-methylpentanoate (CHEBI:55535) is the conjugate base of (R)-2-hydroxy-4-methylpentanoic acid (CHEBI:55534).\\n\\n\\nSo....I think GO:0043713 (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate dehydrogenase activity should be obsoleted and replaced by GO:0140175 (2R)-2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity\\n\\nGO:0043713 (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate dehydrogenase activity has 0 annotations anyway.\",\n  \"comments\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABAn3fSg\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"raymond91125\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"Dear all, \\n\\nThe proposal has been made to obsolete GO:0043713 (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate dehydrogenase activity.\\n\\n* The reason for obsoletion is that this term is equivalent to GO:0140175 (2R)-2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity.\\n\\nThere are no experimental annotations to this term.\\nThere are X InterPro2GO/UniRule/UniProtKW mappings to this term. \\nThis term is not present in any subset.\\n\\nThis term is being replaced by GO:0140175 (2R)-2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity\\n\\nIf obsolete term has a 'consider' term:  (optional)\\nAnnotations can be transferred to [suggested GO term(s)] \\n\\nAny comments can be  added to the issue: [link to GitHub ticket in the go-ontology tracker]. \\nUnless objections are received by [DATE], we will assume that you agree to this change.\\n\\nThanks, \\n\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-28T15:34:45Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31966#issuecomment-4336770890\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABAn4Mfg\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"raymond91125\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please obsolete GO:0043713 (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate dehydrogenase activity.\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-28T15:36:15Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [\n        {\n          \"content\": \"EYES\",\n          \"users\": {\n            \"totalCount\": 1\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31966#issuecomment-4336782462\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABAn4YLg\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"dragon-ai-agent\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"🤖 Working on it...\\n\\nFollow along: [View workflow run](https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/actions/runs/25062447162)\\n\\n*— @dragon-ai-agent*\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-28T15:36:39Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31966#issuecomment-4336785454\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": true\n    }\n  ],\n  \"title\": \"Obsolete GO:0043713 (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate dehydrogenase activity\",\n  \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31966\"\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_1","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/.agents/skills/design-pattern/SKILL.md\"","aggregated_output":"---\nname: design-pattern\ndescription: Use this skill when planning to create new ontology terms or modify existing ones to ensure proper design pattern compliance. This skill should be used proactively during issue planning to identify appropriate design patterns before term creation begins. No intersection_of tags should be added without using this skill.\n---\n\nDesign Patterns (DPs) are designed to ensure that labels, text definitions (def tags), logical definitions (intersection_of tags) are consistent *within* a term, and *across* terms. i.e. a term \"X development\" uses \"X\" in the label, definition, and logical definition (but prioritizing human readability over robotic conformance); and that \"X development\" terms look similar in form to \"X development\" terms.\n\nDesign patterns are documented here, using the DOSDP system:\n\n`src/patterns/*.yaml`\n\nThis skill should provide documentation in the form of a DESIGN_PATTERNS.md doc (not committed) that document relevant DPs for the task at hand.\n\nDP documentation may be incomplete or out of date, so always check for similar terms / precedent using `obo-grep.pl`.\n\nSide Note: CHEBI has particular rules. Always use the /chemical-entity skill for anything involving chemical entities.\n\n## Example: cell fate commitment\n\nConsider this GO term:\n\n```obo\nid: GO:0001710\nname: mesodermal cell fate commitment\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The cell differentiation process that results in commitment of a cell to become part of the mesoderm.\" [GOC:go_curators, ISBN:0878932437]\nsynonym: \"mesoderm cell fate commitment\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0060795 ! cell fate commitment involved in formation of primary germ layer\nintersection_of: GO:0045165 ! cell fate commitment\nintersection_of: results_in_commitment_to CL:0000222 ! mesodermal cell\nrelationship: part_of GO:0048333 ! mesodermal cell differentiation\n```\n\nThis corresponds to this DP: `src/design_patterns/cell_fate_commitment.yaml`, which defines a variable 'target' that must be a type of cell:\n\n```\nvars:\n  target: \"'cell'\"\nclasses:\n  cell: \"CL:0000000\" # Should ensure plant cells are subclasses\n```\n\nIt also defines lexical patterns:\n\n```\nname:\n  text: \"%s cell fate commitment\"\n```\n\n=> the `name` tag is consistent with this\n\n```\ndef:\n  text: \"The process involved in the commitment of %s cell identity.\"\n```\n\n=> the GO definition varies a little from this but is still essentially consistent\n\nAnd a logical definition pattern:\n\n```\nequivalentTo:\n  text: \"'cell fate commitment' and 'results in commitment of' some %s\"\n  vars:\n    - target\n```\n\nThe OWL expression `equivalentTo G and R some D` maps to\n\n```\nintersection_of: G\nintersection_of: R D\n```\n\n## General guidelines\n\nYou should not add logical definitions unless the term truly corresponds to a DP (or if a user really wants you to). A common anti-pattern is over-specifying logical definition (intersection_of), not realizing these are necessary *and sufficient* conditions. If in doubt, it is better to specify necessary only (is_a and intersection_of).\n\n## Inference of is_a\n\nWhen intersection_of is specified, it's generally not necessary to specify an is_a parent because this can be inferred.\n\nThis can be checked via:\n\n`cd src/ontology && robot reason -i go-edit.obo -o go-edit.entailed.obo` and checking the is_a parent\n\n## Creation of DESIGN_PATTERNS.md doc\n\nThe output of this skill can be a document DESIGN_PATTERNS.md that lists and gives examples from the DP docs and existing ontology precedent, this doc will be used to guide term creation and updates, and to provide justification.\n\nNote this document is temporary, it should not be committed, and do not waste time documenting DPs in *general*, this doc is for specifyng relevant DPs to the *task in hand*\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
